@node history "History"
History :
~~~~~~~~~
 v0.5 : No big deal ; it was just an ordinary input/output program.

 v0.6 : Never saw the light. :-)

 v0.7 : Inputs reduced to one file. This is much handier.

 v0.8 : Added quotation. TTest will tell you how many of your answers
        were correct. It'll give you marks as if it was a real exam.

 v0.9 : User input couldn't be compared to the File input. It worked
        fine under UNIX, but not with AmigaDOS. Thanks C= ... :-(
        (and thanks Raf for correcting it, but in the wrong line :)

 v1.0 : First Public Release.

 v1.1 : Code had become much smaller. Thanks Raf !
        Percent-option added. TTest will show the % correct answers.

@endnode
                   
